@startuml federated_cloud_application
title Federated Cloud Application Architecture\nApplication services placed across clouds where each placement is most advantageous

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontName "Helvetica"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam roundcorner 6
skinparam component {
  BackgroundColor #EAF2F8
  BorderColor #2874A6
}
skinparam cloud {
  BackgroundColor #F4ECF7
  BorderColor #6C3483
}

cloud "Cloud A" as cA {
  component "Cloud Application\nService A" as svcA
  component "Cloud Application\nService B" as svcB
  component "Cloud Application\nService C" as svcC
}

cloud "Cloud B" as cB {
  component "AI Service A" as ai
  component "Cloud Application\nService D" as svcD
}

cloud "Cloud C" as cC {
  component "Logging Service A" as log
  component "Cloud Application\nService E" as svcE
}

svcA -right-> ai
svcB -right-> log
svcC -down-> svcD
svcD -right-> svcE

note right of cA
  Each service is deployed where
  the host environment best fits
  its requirements:
  - high-performance compute,
  - resiliency,
  - favorable usage costs,
  - specialized services
    (AI, logging, etc.).
end note

note left of cC
  Distributed parts may also reside
  in on-premises environments.
  This improves outcomes but
  introduces architectural
  complexity.
end note

@enduml
